AUDIO: 'Hello. So, today I\'m going to go through my AI assisted development workflow. So, this was actually adopted by a engineering team at a $4 billion unicorn on a VAPI replacement project I was doing last month. And I didn\'t actually know anyone was using it until they asked me to present'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it division-wide. So, if you\'ve tried AI coding tools for anything serious, you\'ll have noticed that they don\'t really deliver out of the box. They hallucinate, lack context, and they produce generic code.'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, if you\'re using them for simple stuff like auto-complete, scaffolding, stuff like that, you might be wondering what you\'re missing when people claim they have like 10 times productivity on this stuff. And don\'t know about 10x productivity, but'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the missing piece is really the workflow that you build around them, which is where you teach it your own development processes. And that\'s what we\'re going to go through today. So, I must say that I\'ve never personally used Claude Code without any of these context management'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'systems built in, cuz I carried over knowledge from using Cursor, then Wind Surf, then Cursor again. I tried some of the builder platforms like Lovable, Bolton, V naught, and those are okay, but when Claude Code'

